select advanced partitioning

delete C:

click on add and set your size  and set it as primary partition selectin as mount point
/

then add home folder clicking on add
and select as mount
/home

the partition will be logic (don't change as primary)

creating the separated 'home' folder is possible to reinstall the system without touching data
you will have only to reinstall the system formatting only the partition containing
the file system "/"

as last thing set swap area clicking on add and adding like 1 gb of space if you have
1 gb of ram or 2 if you have 2 gb  of ram

set as mount point "swap area" and click ok.

then on the bottom it will appear the selection for the boot loader

you will have to leave it in /dev/sda (not sda1 or sda2)
